body:
### Current Behaviour

Objective: To resolve the issue of displaying Chinese characters in Seaborn and WordCloud.
I modified visualisation\context.py by adding a new value 'Microsoft YaHei' to the font.sans-serif list.
I also modified seaborn\rcmod.py by adding 'Microsoft YaHei' to the font.sans-serif list.
At this point, the Chinese characters in the heatmap displayed in the report were shown correctly.
However, after further modifications:
In visualisation\plot.py, I changed the wordcloud to:
Python
wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", random_state=123, width=300, height=200, scale=2, font_path=r'C:\Windows\Fonts\simhei.ttf').generate_from_frequencies(word_dict)
After this change, the Chinese characters in the heatmap were no longer displayed correctly, while the word cloud was displayed correctly.

### Expected Behaviour

Objective: To resolve the issue of displaying Chinese characters in Seaborn and WordCloud.
I modified visualisation\context.py by adding a new value 'Microsoft YaHei' to the font.sans-serif list.
I also modified seaborn\rcmod.py by adding 'Microsoft YaHei' to the font.sans-serif list.
At this point, the Chinese characters in the heatmap displayed in the report were shown correctly.
However, after further modifications:
In visualisation\plot.py, I changed the wordcloud to:
Python
wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", random_state=123, width=300, height=200, scale=2, font_path=r'C:\Windows\Fonts\simhei.ttf').generate_from_frequencies(word_dict)
After this change, the Chinese characters in the heatmap were no longer displayed correctly, while the word cloud was displayed correctly.

